{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Why can't we solve these problems?"},{"time":6000,"text":"We know what they are."},{"time":9000,"text":"Something always seems to stop us."},{"time":13000,"text":"Why?"},{"time":16000,"text":"I remember March the 15th, 2000."},{"time":20000,"text":"The B15 iceberg broke off the Ross Ice Shelf."},{"time":24000,"text":"In the newspaper it said"},{"time":27000,"text":"\"it was all part of a normal process.\""},{"time":30000,"text":"A little bit further on in the article"},{"time":33000,"text":"it said \"a loss that would normally take"},{"time":36000,"text":"the ice shelf 50-100 years to replace.\""},{"time":43000,"text":"That same word, \"normal,\""},{"time":46000,"text":"had two different,"},{"time":48000,"text":"almost opposite meanings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"If we walk into the B15 iceberg"},{"time":54000,"text":"when we leave here today,"},{"time":57000,"text":"we're going to bump into something"},{"time":60000,"text":"a thousand feet tall,"},{"time":62000,"text":"76 miles long,"},{"time":66000,"text":"17 miles wide,"},{"time":69000,"text":"and it's going to weigh two gigatons."},{"time":72000,"text":"I'm sorry, there's nothing normal about this."},{"time":75000,"text":"And yet I think it's this perspective of us"},{"time":78000,"text":"as humans to look at our world"},{"time":81000,"text":"through the lens of normal"},{"time":83000,"text":"is one of the forces"},{"time":85000,"text":"that stops us developing real solutions."},{"time":91000,"text":"Only 90 days after this,"},{"time":94000,"text":"arguably the greatest discovery"},{"time":96000,"text":"of the last century occurred."},{"time":98000,"text":"It was the sequencing for the first time"},{"time":100000,"text":"of the human genome."},{"time":103000,"text":"This is the code that's in every single one"},{"time":107000,"text":"of our 50 trillion cells"},{"time":109000,"text":"that makes us who we are and what we are."},{"time":113000,"text":"And if we just take one cell's worth"},{"time":115000,"text":"of this code and unwind it,"},{"time":120000,"text":"it's a meter long,"},{"time":124000,"text":"two nanometers thick."},{"time":126000,"text":"Two nanometers is 20 atoms in thickness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"And I wondered,"},{"time":132000,"text":"what if the answer to some of our biggest problems"},{"time":135000,"text":"could be found in the smallest of places,"},{"time":138000,"text":"where the difference between what is"},{"time":140000,"text":"valuable and what is worthless"},{"time":142000,"text":"is merely the addition or subtraction"},{"time":144000,"text":"of a few atoms?"},{"time":146000,"text":"And what"},{"time":148000,"text":"if we could get exquisite control"},{"time":151000,"text":"over the essence of energy,"},{"time":153000,"text":"the electron?"},{"time":156000,"text":"So I started to go around the world"},{"time":158000,"text":"finding the best and brightest scientists"},{"time":160000,"text":"I could at universities"},{"time":162000,"text":"whose collective discoveries have the chance"},{"time":164000,"text":"to take us there,"},{"time":166000,"text":"and we formed a company to build"},{"time":168000,"text":"on their extraordinary ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"Six and a half years later,"},{"time":172000,"text":"a hundred and eighty researchers,"},{"time":174000,"text":"they have some amazing developments"},{"time":176000,"text":"in the lab,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and I will show you three of those today,"},{"time":180000,"text":"such that we can stop burning up our planet"},{"time":183000,"text":"and instead,"},{"time":185000,"text":"we can generate all the energy we need"},{"time":188000,"text":"right where we are,"},{"time":190000,"text":"cleanly, safely, and cheaply."},{"time":193000,"text":"Think of the space that we spend"},{"time":195000,"text":"most of our time."},{"time":197000,"text":"A tremendous amount of energy"},{"time":199000,"text":"is coming at us from the sun."},{"time":201000,"text":"We like the light that comes into the room,"},{"time":203000,"text":"but in the middle of summer,"},{"time":205000,"text":"all that heat is coming into the room"},{"time":207000,"text":"that we're trying to keep cool."},{"time":209000,"text":"In winter, exactly the opposite is happening."},{"time":211000,"text":"We're trying to heat up"},{"time":212000,"text":"the space that we're in,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and all that is trying to get out through the window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"Wouldn't it be really great"},{"time":220000,"text":"if the window could flick back the heat"},{"time":222000,"text":"into the room if we needed it"},{"time":224000,"text":"or flick it away before it came in?"},{"time":226000,"text":"One of the materials that can do this"},{"time":228000,"text":"is a remarkable material, carbon,"},{"time":233000,"text":"that has changed its form in this incredibly beautiful reaction"},{"time":236000,"text":"where graphite is blasted by a vapor,"},{"time":241000,"text":"and when the vaporized carbon condenses,"},{"time":245000,"text":"it condenses back into a different form:"},{"time":248000,"text":"chickenwire rolled up."},{"time":251000,"text":"But this chickenwire carbon,"},{"time":253000,"text":"called a carbon nanotube,"},{"time":255000,"text":"is a hundred thousand times smaller"},{"time":257000,"text":"than the width of one of your hairs."},{"time":260000,"text":"It's a thousand times"},{"time":262000,"text":"more conductive than copper."},{"time":265000,"text":"How is that possible?"},{"time":270000,"text":"One of the things about working at the nanoscale"},{"time":274000,"text":"is things look and act very differently."},{"time":277000,"text":"You think of carbon as black."},{"time":283000,"text":"Carbon at the nanoscale"},{"time":286000,"text":"is actually transparent"},{"time":289000,"text":"and flexible."},{"time":294000,"text":"And when it's in this form,"},{"time":296000,"text":"if I combine it with a polymer"},{"time":299000,"text":"and affix it to your window"},{"time":302000,"text":"when it's in its colored state,"},{"time":305000,"text":"it will reflect away all heat and light,"},{"time":308000,"text":"and when it's in its bleached state"},{"time":310000,"text":"it will let all the light and heat through"},{"time":313000,"text":"and any combination in between."},{"time":316000,"text":"To change its state, by the way,"},{"time":319000,"text":"takes two volts from a millisecond pulse."},{"time":322000,"text":"And once you've changed its state, it stays there"},{"time":325000,"text":"until you change its state again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"As we were working on this incredible"},{"time":330000,"text":"discovery at University of Florida,"},{"time":332000,"text":"we were told to go down the corridor"},{"time":335000,"text":"to visit another scientist,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and he was working"},{"time":339000,"text":"on a pretty incredible thing."},{"time":341000,"text":"Imagine"},{"time":343000,"text":"if we didn't have to rely"},{"time":345000,"text":"on artificial lighting to get around at night."},{"time":351000,"text":"We'd have to see at night, right?"},{"time":357000,"text":"This lets you do it."},{"time":359000,"text":"It's a nanomaterial, two nanomaterials,"},{"time":362000,"text":"a detector and an imager."},{"time":365000,"text":"The total width of it"},{"time":367000,"text":"is 600 times smaller"},{"time":369000,"text":"than the width of a decimal place."},{"time":372000,"text":"And it takes all the infrared available at night,"},{"time":376000,"text":"converts it into an electron"},{"time":379000,"text":"in the space of two small films,"},{"time":382000,"text":"and is enabling you to play an image"},{"time":385000,"text":"which you can see through."},{"time":392000,"text":"I'm going to show to TEDsters,"},{"time":395000,"text":"the first time, this operating."},{"time":397000,"text":"Firstly I'm going to show you"},{"time":399000,"text":"the transparency."},{"time":402000,"text":"Transparency is key."},{"time":406000,"text":"It's a film that you can look through."},{"time":409000,"text":"And then I'm going to turn the lights out."},{"time":412000,"text":"And you can see, off a tiny film,"},{"time":415000,"text":"incredible clarity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"As we were working on this, it dawned on us:"},{"time":423000,"text":"this is taking infrared radiation, wavelengths,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and converting it into electrons."},{"time":430000,"text":"What if we combined it"},{"time":436000,"text":"with this?"},{"time":439000,"text":"Suddenly you've converted energy"},{"time":442000,"text":"into an electron on a plastic surface"},{"time":446000,"text":"that you can stick on your window."},{"time":449000,"text":"But because it's flexible,"},{"time":451000,"text":"it can be on any surface whatsoever."},{"time":455000,"text":"The power plant of tomorrow"},{"time":458000,"text":"is no power plant."},{"time":465000,"text":"We talked about generating and using."},{"time":468000,"text":"We want to talk about storing energy,"},{"time":470000,"text":"and unfortunately"},{"time":472000,"text":"the best thing we've got going"},{"time":474000,"text":"is something that was developed in France"},{"time":476000,"text":"a hundred and fifty years ago,"},{"time":478000,"text":"the lead acid battery."},{"time":480000,"text":"In terms of dollars per what's stored,"},{"time":482000,"text":"it's simply the best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"Knowing that we're not going to put fifty of"},{"time":486000,"text":"these in our basements to store our power,"},{"time":488000,"text":"we went to a group at University of Texas at Dallas,"},{"time":490000,"text":"and we gave them this diagram."},{"time":492000,"text":"It was in actually a diner"},{"time":494000,"text":"outside of Dallas/Fort Worth Airport."},{"time":496000,"text":"We said, \"Could you build this?\""},{"time":498000,"text":"And these scientists,"},{"time":500000,"text":"instead of laughing at us, said, \"Yeah.\""},{"time":502000,"text":"And what they built was eBox."},{"time":505000,"text":"EBox is testing new nanomaterials"},{"time":507000,"text":"to park an electron on the outside,"},{"time":510000,"text":"hold it until you need it,"},{"time":513000,"text":"and then be able to release it and pass it off."},{"time":516000,"text":"Being able to do that means"},{"time":520000,"text":"that I can generate energy"},{"time":523000,"text":"cleanly, efficiently and cheaply"},{"time":526000,"text":"right where I am."},{"time":528000,"text":"It's my energy."},{"time":531000,"text":"And if I don't need it, I can convert it"},{"time":533000,"text":"back up on the window"},{"time":535000,"text":"to energy, light, and beam it,"},{"time":537000,"text":"line of site, to your place."},{"time":540000,"text":"And for that I do not need"},{"time":543000,"text":"an electric grid between us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546000,"text":"The grid of tomorrow is no grid,"},{"time":550000,"text":"and energy, clean efficient energy,"},{"time":554000,"text":"will one day be free."},{"time":561000,"text":"If you do this, you get the last puzzle piece,"},{"time":565000,"text":"which is water."},{"time":571000,"text":"Each of us, every day,"},{"time":576000,"text":"need just eight glasses of this,"},{"time":581000,"text":"because we're human."},{"time":584000,"text":"When we run out of water,"},{"time":586000,"text":"as we are in some parts of the world"},{"time":588000,"text":"and soon to be in other parts of the world,"},{"time":590000,"text":"we're going to have to get this from the sea,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and that's going to require us to build desalination plants."},{"time":596000,"text":"19 trillion dollars is what we're going to have to spend."},{"time":599000,"text":"These also require tremendous amounts of energy."},{"time":601000,"text":"In fact, it's going to require twice the world's"},{"time":603000,"text":"supply of oil to run the pumps"},{"time":605000,"text":"to generate the water."},{"time":608000,"text":"We're simply not going to do that."},{"time":610000,"text":"But in a world where energy is freed"},{"time":612000,"text":"and transmittable"},{"time":614000,"text":"easily and cheaply, we can take any water"},{"time":616000,"text":"wherever we are"},{"time":618000,"text":"and turn it into whatever we need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"I'm glad to be working with"},{"time":624000,"text":"incredibly brilliant and kind scientists,"},{"time":626000,"text":"no kinder than"},{"time":628000,"text":"many of the people in the world,"},{"time":630000,"text":"but they have a magic look at the world."},{"time":633000,"text":"And I'm glad to see their discoveries"},{"time":635000,"text":"coming out of the lab and into the world."},{"time":638000,"text":"It's been a long time in coming for me."},{"time":642000,"text":"18 years ago,"},{"time":645000,"text":"I saw a photograph in the paper."},{"time":649000,"text":"It was taken by Kevin Carter"},{"time":651000,"text":"who went to the Sudan"},{"time":653000,"text":"to document their famine there."},{"time":655000,"text":"I've carried this photograph with me"},{"time":657000,"text":"every day since then."},{"time":662000,"text":"It's a picture of a little girl dying of thirst."},{"time":672000,"text":"By any standard this is wrong."},{"time":677000,"text":"It's just wrong."},{"time":683000,"text":"We can do better than this."},{"time":686000,"text":"We should do better than this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689000,"text":"And whenever I go round"},{"time":691000,"text":"to somebody who says,"},{"time":693000,"text":"\"You know what, you're working on something that's too difficult."},{"time":695000,"text":"It'll never happen. You don't have enough money."},{"time":698000,"text":"You don't have enough time."},{"time":701000,"text":"There's something much more interesting around the corner,\""},{"time":704000,"text":"I say, \"Try saying that to her.\""},{"time":706000,"text":"That's what I say in my mind. And I just say"},{"time":708000,"text":"\"thank you,\" and I go on to the next one."},{"time":711000,"text":"This is why we have to solve our problems,"},{"time":714000,"text":"and I know the answer as to how"},{"time":719000,"text":"is to be able to get exquisite control"},{"time":723000,"text":"over a building block of nature,"},{"time":726000,"text":"the stuff of life:"},{"time":728000,"text":"the simple electron."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}